8:[["$","main",null,{"className":"px-4 md:px-0","children":[["$","section",null,{"children":[["$","h1",null,{"className":"font-semibold tracking-tight text-4xl text-slate-900","children":"Monorepo Setup with Next.js and Turborepo"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-slate-500 text-sm tracking-tight font-mono block mt-4","children":["Published on"," ",["$","time",null,{"dateTime":"2025-05-18","children":"18 May 2025"}]]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"py-5","children":["$","article",null,{"className":"prose prose-lg","children":"$L13"}]}]]}],["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"BlogPosting\",\"headline\":\"Monorepo Setup with Next.js and Turborepo\",\"url\":\"https://saurabhcoded.github.io/posts/monorepo-setup\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-05-18\",\"dateModified\":\"2025-05-18\",\"author\":[{\"@type\":\"Person\",\"name\":\"Saurabh Sharma\",\"url\":\"https://saurabhcoded.github.io\"}]}"}}]]
13:[["$","p",null,{"children":["When I started building Starkie AI, my ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://starkie.ai","children":"AI Photo"}]," project, I quickly found myself juggling a next.js frontend, an express API, and various UI and DB utilities. Maintaining them in separate repos felt messy: version mismatches, linking pain, duplicated configs. So I migrated into a monorepo setup that’s stayed clean and manageable ever since. In this post, I’ll walk through ",["$","em",null,{"children":"how I structure things"}],", ",["$","em",null,{"children":"which tools make sense"}],", and ",["$","em",null,{"children":"the little tricks"}]," I picked up along the way."]}],"\n",["$","hr",null,{}],"\n",["$","h3",null,{"children":"1. Why a Monorepo"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"I didn’t adopt a monorepo because it’s the “right architecture” or because everyone does it. I did it because:"}],"\n",["$","ul",null,{"children":["\n",["$","li",null,{"children":"I have multiple deployable apps (frontend, admin app, API) that share code (UI components, types, helper logic)."}],"\n"]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"So monorepo here is a pragmatic choice, not a posture. If your project is just a single microservice, it probably doesn’t need this. But once you cross the “two apps + shared bits” threshold, it’s a nice guardrail."}],"\n",["$","hr",null,{}],"\n",["$","h3",null,{"children":"2. The Layout (and Why It Feels Right)"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"Here’s (roughly) what my repo looks like:"}],"\n",["$","pre",null,{"children":["$","code",null,{"children":"apps/\n  admin/\n  frontend/\n  api/\npackages/\n  prisma/\n  ui/\n.env.local\ndocker-compose.yml\npnpm-workspace.yaml\ntsconfig.json\nturbo.json\neslint.config.mjs\n…\n"}]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["$","em",null,{"children":["A small note on this, I've also experimented having all of my apps and packages at the root level (",["$","code",null,{"children":"app.admin"}],", ",["$","code",null,{"children":"app.frontend"}],"), however I found that some AI tools like Cursor seem to prefer having a directory to work in"]}]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["$","strong",null,{"children":"What each folder means:"}]}],"\n",["$","ul",null,{"children":["\n",["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","code",null,{"children":"apps/"}]," — These are the ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"deployable"}]," projects. E.g. My two next.js frontends and my API."]}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","code",null,{"children":"packages/"}]," — Shared modules: UI component library, Prisma client/lib, utility logic, etc."]}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"children":"Root-level config files — workspace setup, build orchestration, linting, types, etc."}],"\n"]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["I like this layout because it’s predictable: if I need shared logic, it lives in ",["$","code",null,{"children":"packages"}],". If I need a new app (e.g. mobile UI), I drop it into ",["$","code",null,{"children":"apps"}],"."]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["One small decision: I keep a per-app ",["$","code",null,{"children":".env.local"}]," (or equivalent) rather than a global ",["$","code",null,{"children":".env"}]," that spans everything. Makes it safer when switching context."]}],"\n",["$","hr",null,{}],"\n",["$","h3",null,{"children":"3. Key Tools That Glue It Together"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["Here’s what really makes this setup work ",["$","em",null,{"children":"without breaking my brain"}],":"]}],"\n",["$","ul",null,{"children":["\n",["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"pnpm workspaces"}]," — fast installs, and local linking of packages works out of the box."]}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Turborepo"}]," — orchestrates build, lint, test pipelines across apps and packages. I don’t have to reinvent orchestration."]}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"TypeScript project references / shared tsconfig"}]," — helps incremental builds, ensures that packages depend on each other correctly."]}],"\n","$L14","\n","$L15","\n","$L16","\n"]}],"\n","$L17","\n","$L18","\n","$L19","\n","$L1a","\n","$L1b","\n","$L1c","\n","$L1d","\n","$L1e","\n","$L1f","\n","$L20","\n","$L21","\n","$L22"]
14:["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Local packages"}]," (e.g. ",["$","code",null,{"children":"@ui"}],", ",["$","code",null,{"children":"@utils"}],") — so inside my apps I can do ",["$","code",null,{"children":" import {Button} from '@starkie/ui'"}]," seamlessly."]}]
15:["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"ESLint / Prettier at root"}]," — unified style across all apps and packages."]}]
16:["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Docker / docker-compose"}]," — gives me quick access to a postgres database locally"]}]
17:["$","p",null,{"children":"With these, I can run:"}]
18:["$","pre",null,{"children":["$","code",null,{"className":"hljs language-bash","children":"pnpm install\npnpm turbo run dev\n"}]}]
19:["$","p",null,{"children":"… and everything spins up (frontend, backend, UI watchers) without extra scripts per folder."}]
1a:["$","hr",null,{}]
1b:["$","h3",null,{"children":"4. Tiny Tricks That Save My Sanity"}]
1c:["$","p",null,{"children":"Here are small habits and tweaks I’ve learned that make a big difference:"}]
1d:["$","ul",null,{"children":["\n",["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Selective pipelines"}]," — in ",["$","code",null,{"children":"turbo.json"}],", skip building apps/packages that haven’t changed (incremental)."]}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":["Use ",["$","code",null,{"children":"prebuild"}]," or ",["$","code",null,{"children":"prepare"}]," hooks"]}]," in packages that generate code (e.g. Prisma client), so downstream apps get fresh artifacts."]}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Pin package versions at root"}]," — avoid subtle mismatches (e.g. React version drift)."]}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Explicit dependency direction"}],": packages under ",["$","code",null,{"children":"packages/"}]," should depend ",["$","em",null,{"children":"only"}]," “downwards” or on external libs; they should ",["$","em",null,{"children":"not"}]," depend on apps. Keeps the architecture clean."]}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Lint imports"}]," — disallow relative imports that skip ",["$","code",null,{"children":"packages"}]," boundaries; force you to use workspace boundaries."]}],"\n"]}]
1e:["$","hr",null,{}]
1f:["$","h3",null,{"children":"5. Future"}]
20:["$","p",null,{"children":"This monorepo isn't perfect, but it's where I'm currently at from scaling a side project to an actual product with customers."}]
21:["$","p",null,{"children":"It's helped me ship faster, cut down on duplicated code, and stay sane as the project grows."}]
22:["$","p",null,{"children":"If you’re starting a project with multiple moving pieces, I’d encourage you to try a lean monorepo early - you can always break it apart later if complexity truly demands it."}]
